{
  "texts": [
    "Nevertheless, some GNN relay models, employed for encoding both structure and feature information, inevitably result in a loss of structural information and create an entanglement between the condensed graph and the relay model.",
    "These issues significantly affect the generalization ability to unseen models and tasks.",
    "To explore the cause, GDEM [66] conducts an investigation across various GNN architectures, including different spatial and spectral GNNs.",
    "They find that the performance gap increases when the relay model and downstream model have different architectures.",
    "This is due to that distinct spectral preferences of GNNs have varying impacts on the significance of different graph eigenvectors [81], [82], consequently leading to alterations in node features."
  ]
}